## Builder Tool Executor — All Setters Must Validate `nodeId` Existence

**Problem:** All setter tools (`set_text`, `set_typography`, `set_text_color`, `set_size`, `set_spacing`, `set_border`, `set_background`, `set_opacity`, `set_position`, `set_layout`, `set_overflow`, `set_animation`, `set_icon`, `rename_node`) call `patchProp` / `patchNodeById` which silently does nothing when no node matches the given `nodeId`. The tool returns `{ success: true }` even though no change occurred — the AI cannot detect the failure and continues building on ghost nodes.

This is most visible when `add_component` fails (e.g. due to an invalid `parentId` string like `"hero-content"` instead of a UUID), and then all subsequent styling calls also silently succeed, producing a hero section that looks complete in the chat log but has no nodes on the canvas.

**Fix (applied in `lib/ai/tool-executor.ts`):** A shared `requireNode` helper is called at the start of every setter:

```ts
function requireNode(store: BuilderStore, nodeId: string | undefined) {
  if (!nodeId) return { success: false, error: 'nodeId is required.' };
  if (!findNode(store.pageNodes as SDUINode[], nodeId)) {
    return {
      success: false,
      error: `Node "${nodeId}" not found on the current page. Call get_page_tree first to get valid node IDs, or check whether a prior add_component step failed.`,
    };
  }
  return null;
}
```

Each setter starts with:
```ts
const nodeErr = requireNode(store, nodeId);
if (nodeErr) return nodeErr;
```

**Rule:** When adding a new setter tool to `lib/ai/tool-executor.ts`, ALWAYS add `requireNode` as the first guard. Never call `patchProp`, `patchNodeById`, or `patchNodeField` without first verifying the node exists.

**Builder chat error display:** Failed steps (`status: "error"`) now show a **red dot** (`#ef4444`) and red label (`#fca5a5`) in the builder chat panel. Previously they showed as blue, making them look like informational items rather than failures. The summary dot in a collapsed tool group also turns red when any step in the group failed.

