## Animated Node `animNodeOwnsId` — Outer Wrapper Style Rule

**Problem:** In builder mode, when a node has an animation config, `animNodeOwnsId` is true and the renderer wraps the element in an `AnimatedNode`. The outer animated wrapper is the selectable/resizable target. A previous bug spread the full `cleanProps.style` (which = `arbStyles` + `node.props.style`) to `outerStyle`, then deleted it from the inner element. This caused:
- Padding that existed in both arbStyles AND compiled CSS classes to be applied twice (outer padding + inner CSS padding), making builder elements taller/wider than preview.
- Non-JIT-compiled arbitrary classes to lose their inline style fallback on the inner element.

**Fix (applied in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx` `animNodeOwnsId` block):**
- `outerFromArb` — only keys in `OUTER_PASSTHROUGH` (`width`, `height`, size constraints, `top`/`right`/`bottom`/`left`, `borderRadius` variants, `zIndex`) from `arbStyles` go to the outer wrapper.
- `nodePropsStyle` — only `node.props.style` (explicit JSON style written by tools like `set_opacity`) goes to the outer wrapper, NOT the full `cleanProps.style`.
- `cleanProps.style` is **not deleted** — the inner element keeps its full arbStyles inline styles so non-compiled arbitrary classes still render.

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT
const outerFromArb: Record<string, unknown> = {};
for (const key of OUTER_PASSTHROUGH) {
  if (key in arbStyles) outerFromArb[key] = arbStyles[key];
}
const nodePropsStyle = (node.props?.style ?? {}) as Record<string, unknown>;
const styleForOuter = { ...outerFromArb, ...nodePropsStyle };
// Do NOT delete cleanProps.style

// ❌ WRONG — caused double padding and lost inline styles
const innerStyle = cleanProps.style; // includes arbStyles padding!
const styleForOuter = { ...outerFromArb, ...innerStyle }; // padding leaks to outer
delete cleanProps.style; // inner loses inline style fallback
```

**Rule:** When modifying the `animNodeOwnsId` block in `renderer.tsx`, never spread the full `cleanProps.style` into `outerStyle` and never delete `cleanProps.style` from the inner element.

